                      <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>3</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000K/</fr:uri>
                    <fr:display-uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000K</fr:display-uri>
                    <fr:route>/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000K/</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Full and faithful functor">Full and faithful <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000I/" title="Functor between precategories" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000I/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000I" type="local">functor</fr:link></fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                    <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000K.agda" type="external">erct-000K.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <html:p>A <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000I/" title="Functor between precategories" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000I/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000I" type="local">functor</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F\colon  C \to  D]]></fr:tex> is called (<html:em><html:strong>full</html:strong></html:em>, <html:em><html:strong>faithful</html:strong></html:em>) when the action on arrows is valued in (<fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0029/" title="Surjection" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0029/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0029" type="local">surjections</fr:link>, <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-003K/" title="Embedding" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-003K/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-003K" type="local">embeddings</fr:link>) respectively. It is common to refer to a <html:em>full</html:em> and <html:em>faithful</html:em> functor as <html:em><html:strong>fully faithful</html:strong></html:em>.</html:p>
                    <html:p>Fullness and faithfulness are both <html:em><fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I/" title="Proposition" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I" type="local">properties</fr:link></html:em> of a functor.</html:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>3</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000J/</fr:uri>
                    <fr:display-uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000J</fr:display-uri>
                    <fr:route>/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000J/</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Isomorphism of precategories">Isomorphism of <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" title="Precategory" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B" type="local">precategories</fr:link></fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                    <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000J.agda" type="external">erct-000J.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <html:p>A <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000I/" title="Functor between precategories" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000I/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000I" type="local">functor</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F\colon  C \to  D]]></fr:tex> is called an <html:em><html:strong>isomorphism</html:strong></html:em>, written <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  C\cong  D]]></fr:tex>, when <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000K/" title="Full and faithful functor" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000K/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000K" type="local">fully faithful</fr:link> and its action on objects is an equivalence of types.</html:p>
                    <html:p>Being an isomorphism is a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I/" title="Proposition" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>.</html:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>3</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000L/</fr:uri>
                    <fr:display-uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000L</fr:display-uri>
                    <fr:route>/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000L/</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="The univalence principle for precategories">The univalence principle for <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" title="Precategory" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B" type="local">precategories</fr:link></fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
                    <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000L.agda" type="external">erct-000L.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>For any <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" title="Precategory" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B" type="local">precategory</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex>, the type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen D : \mathsf {Precategory}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen D : \mathsf {Precategory}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen D : \mathsf {Precategory}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen D : \mathsf {Precategory}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{D\cong  C}]]></fr:tex> of <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000J/" title="Isomorphism of precategories" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000J/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000J" type="local">isomorphisms of precategories</fr:link> onto <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H/" title="Contractible type" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>3</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>The type of isomorphisms onto <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> is inhabited, considering the identity isomorphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{C}\colon  C\cong  C]]></fr:tex>. Therefore, it suffices to show that the type of <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000J/" title="Isomorphism of precategories" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000J/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000J" type="local">isomorphisms</fr:link> onto <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> depicted below is a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I/" title="Proposition" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>:</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
   \begin {aligned}
    D &: \mathsf {Precategory}\\
    F &: D\cong  C
   \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>We unfold the definitions of a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" title="Precategory" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B" type="local">precategories</fr:link> and <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000J/" title="Isomorphism of precategories" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000J/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000J" type="local">their isomorphisms</fr:link>, dropping <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I/" title="Proposition" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001I" type="local">propositional</fr:link> axioms:</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \begin {aligned}
      D_0&: \mathsf {Type}\\
      D_1&:D_0\to  D_0\to \mathsf {Set}\\
      F_0&: D_0\to  C_0\\
      F_1&: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} D_1xy\to  C
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen F_0x,F_0y\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\\
      h_1 &: \mathsf {isBiinvertible}\,F_0\\
      h_2 &: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} \mathsf {isPropMap}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen F_1xy\right \rparen \mathclose {}

      \\
      h_3 &: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} \mathsf {isSurjection}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen F_1xy\right \rparen \mathclose {}

    \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>A function that is both <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001T/" title="n-truncated map" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001T/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001T" type="local">propositional</fr:link> and a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0029/" title="Surjection" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0029/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0029" type="local">surjection</fr:link>, i.e. a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-003F/" title="Bijection" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-003F/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-003F" type="local">bijection</fr:link>, is an <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000V/" title="Equivalence of types" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000V/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000V" type="local">equivalence</fr:link> by <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-002Z/" title="bijections are biinvertible" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-002Z/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-002Z" type="local">Corollary <fr:contextual-number uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-002Z/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-002Z" /></fr:link>. We can therefore repackage our telescope equivalently:</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \begin {aligned}
      D_0&: \mathsf {Type}\\
      D_1&:D_0\to  D_0\to \mathsf {Set}\\
      F_0&: D_0\cong  C_0\\
      F_1&: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y: D_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} D_1xy\cong  C
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen F_0x,F_0y\right \rparen \mathclose {}

    \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>By the univalence principle for types, we may contract 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen D_0,F_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
 to 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen 
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
, 1_{
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
}\right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
:</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \begin {aligned}
      D_1&:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\to  
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\to \mathsf {Set}\\
      F_1&: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} D_1xy\cong  C
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\right \rparen \mathclose {}

    \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>Next we rewrite using the univalence principles for functions and families of types (<fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0015/" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0015/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0015" type="local">Axiom <fr:contextual-number uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0015/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0015" /></fr:link>, <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001D/" title="The univalence principle for types" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001D/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001D" type="local">Axiom <fr:contextual-number uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001D/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001D" /></fr:link>):</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \begin {aligned}
      D_1&:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\to  
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\to \mathsf {Set}\\
      F_1&: D_1 = \lambda {x,y}\mathpunct {.}{C
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}
    \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>By the <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0015/" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0015/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0015" type="local">univalence principle for functions</fr:link>, the data above is <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H/" title="Contractible type" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>31</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0030/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0030</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-0030/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Natural transformation">Natural transformation</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0030.agda" type="external">erct-0030.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" title="Precategory" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B" type="local">precategories</fr:link>, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F,G\colon  C\to  D]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000I/" title="Functor between precategories" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000I/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000I" type="local">functors</fr:link> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>. A <html:em><html:strong>natural transformation</html:strong></html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \colon  F\to  G]]></fr:tex> is given by a family of arrows <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _\bullet \colon \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}D
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen Fx,Gx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex> equipped with a (necessarily unique) naturality datum <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _f\colon  \alpha _y\circ  Ff = Gf\circ  \alpha _x]]></fr:tex> for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  x\to  y]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>3</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000F/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000F</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000F/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Section-retraction pair in a precategory">Section-retraction pair in a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" title="Precategory" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B" type="local">precategory</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A <html:em><html:strong>section-retraction pair</html:strong></html:em> in a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" title="Precategory" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B" type="local">precategory</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> consists of an arrow <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\colon  x \to  y]]></fr:tex> called the <html:em>section</html:em> and an arrow <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\colon  y \to  x]]></fr:tex> called the <html:em>retraction</html:em> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\circ  s = 1_{x}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>3</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000G/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000G</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000G/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Isomorphism in a precategory">Isomorphism in a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" title="Precategory" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B" type="local">precategory</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000G.agda" type="external">erct-000G.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>An arrow <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  x \to  y]]></fr:tex> in a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" title="Precategory" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B" type="local">precategory</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> is called an <html:em><html:strong>isomorphism</html:strong></html:em> when either of there exists an inverse to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>, i.e. an arrow <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  y \to  x]]></fr:tex> that is simultaneously a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000F/" title="Section-retraction pair in a precategory" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000F/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000F" type="local">section and a retraction</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
                <html:p>We shall write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  x \cong  y]]></fr:tex> to denote an isomorphism from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>3</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000D/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000D</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000D/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Univalent precategory">Univalent <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" title="Precategory" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B" type="local">precategory</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000D.agda" type="external">erct-000D.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" title="Precategory" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B" type="local">precategory</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> is called <html:em><html:strong>univalent</html:strong></html:em> when for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  C]]></fr:tex>, the type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \sum _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y\in  C\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}y\cong  x]]></fr:tex> of <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000G/" title="Isomorphism in a precategory" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000G/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000G" type="local">isomorphisms</fr:link> onto <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H/" title="Contractible type" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
