  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000H.agda" type="external">erct-000H.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A <html:em><html:strong>category</html:strong></html:em> is defined to be a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000D/" title="Univalent precategory" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000D/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000D" type="local">univalent</fr:link> <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" title="Precategory" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000B" type="local">precategory</fr:link>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <html:p>The material on univalent category theory is drawn primarily from the <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/hottbook/" title="Homotopy Type Theory: univalent foundations of mathematics" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/hottbook/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/hottbook" type="local">HoTT Book</fr:link> and <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/ahrens-kapulkin-shulman-2015/" title="Univalent categories and the Rezk completion" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/ahrens-kapulkin-shulman-2015/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/ahrens-kapulkin-shulman-2015" type="local">Ahrens, Kapulkin, and Shulman</fr:link>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
